metadata.title: RESEARCH: Vulnerable Unquoted Service Path (registry)
metadata.description:
A registry event associated with a Windows service with an unquoted service path vulnerability was identified. This activity may indicate that an exploitable service is present on this system that allows threat actors to escalate their privileges to the SYSTEM user.

Example:
Unquoted Service Image Path: C:\Program Files\Vk9 Security\binary files\executable files\real-program.exe
Exploit Process Image Path: C:\Program Files\Vk9 Security\binary files\executable.exe

metadata.title: WinRAR Spawns Child Process
metadata.description:
A process event associated with a child process unexpectedly being spawned out of an instance of WinRAR was identified. This may indicate that a malicious attacker or program is active on the host system.

Example:
> WinRar.exe Compressed.rar
 -> PossiblyMalware.exe

metadata.title: RESEARCH: Security Descriptor Editor in Non-Standard Location (filemod)
metadata.description:
A filemod event associated with the Security Descriptor Editor (Aclui.dll) running from a non-standard directory was identified. This activity may indicate that threat actors are using Aclui.dll to side-load malware.

Example: 
> C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\Temp\Aclui.dll

The expected path for this file is in the "\Windows\System32" directory.
